<td>June 15, 2023
</td>
<td>Passed the CROWN Act, amending the <a href="/wiki/Elliott-Larsen_Civil_Rights_Act" title="Elliott-Larsen Civil Rights Act">Elliott-Larsen Civil Rights Act</a><sup id="cite_ref-34" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-34">&#91;34&#93;</a></sup>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>In addition, similar legislation has been introduced in Florida, Georgia, Kansas, Kentucky, Mississippi, Missouri, Nebraska, New Hampshire, North Carolina, Ohio, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, South Carolina, Utah, and Wisconsin. An executive order prohibiting discrimination by Arizona state agencies and contractors was signed by Governor <a href="/wiki/Katie_Hobbs" title="Katie Hobbs">Katie Hobbs</a> on March 17, 2023.<sup id="cite_ref-35" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-35">&#91;35&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
